.SH NAME
Navigator.mediaDevices \- Navigator: mediaDevices property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]mediaDevices\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Navigator\f[R] interface returns a \f[CR]MediaDevices\f[R] object,
which provides access to connected media input devices like cameras and
microphones, as well as screen sharing.
.SH VALUE
The \f[CR]MediaDevices\f[R] singleton object.
Usually, you just use this object\[cq]s members directly, such as by
calling \f[CR]navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia()\f[R].
